CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 30, 1958, pg. 1, reads: "Grieved Over Mother's Death, Marion Moone, 36, Commits Suicide! Ready for Morgue - Covered with a blanket, the body of 36-year-old Marion Edward Moone, of 2528 Wadsworth Terrace, is ready for the trip to the Allegheny County Morgue, after being discovered early Wednesday morning by Courier Religious Editor Bert H. Logan and four other persons, who while on their way to work, saw the body handing from the front porch."
TitMainTitle: Body of Marion Edward Moone covered with blanket and lying on porch of home at 2528 Wadsworth Terrace, Hill District
